# Google Search Engine Results Page Extraction with Bright Data

## Overview
Automated workflow: Google Search Engine Results Page Extraction with Bright Data. This workflow integrates 10 different services: stickyNote, httpRequest, toolHttpRequest, lmChatGoogleGemini, agent. It contains 19 nodes and follows best practices for error handling and security.

## Workflow Details
- **Total Nodes**: 19
- **Node Types**: 10
- **Error Handling**: ✅ Implemented
- **Security**: ✅ Hardened (no sensitive data)
- **Documentation**: ✅ Complete

## Node Breakdown
- **When clicking ‘Test workflow’**: manualTrigger
- **Google Gemini Chat Model**: lmChatGoogleGemini
- **Summarization Chain**: chainSummarization
- **Google Gemini Chat Model For Summarization**: lmChatGoogleGemini
- **Google Gemini Chat Model1**: lmChatGoogleGemini
- **Webhook HTTP Request**: toolHttpRequest
- **Sticky Note**: stickyNote
- **Sticky Note1**: stickyNote
- **Google Search Data Extractor**: informationExtractor
- **Perform Google Search Request**: httpRequest
- ... and 9 more nodes

## Usage Instructions
1. **Configure Credentials**: Set up all required API keys and credentials
2. **Update Variables**: Replace any placeholder values with actual data
3. **Test Workflow**: Run in test mode to verify functionality
4. **Deploy**: Activate the workflow for production use

## Security Notes
- All sensitive data has been removed or replaced with placeholders
- Error handling is implemented for reliability
- Follow security best practices when configuring credentials

## Troubleshooting
- Check error logs if workflow fails
- Verify all credentials are properly configured
- Ensure all required services are accessible
